  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to evaluate the performance, the tolerability and the efficacy on
      gas-exchange of different CPAP (Continuous Positive Airway Pressure) systems.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Three CPAP systems are studied for each patient at the same level of PEEP: 1) continuous
      high-flow CPAP with fixed value PEEP valve; 2) continuous high-flow CPAP with Boussignac PEEP
      valve; 3) demand flow CPAP, supplied by a ventilator.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
